\parindent 0pt \parskip 6pt
\vspace{-20pt}

\begin{enumerate}

\item\label{one} Compute an initial coarse $\zeta$ grid as the union of
the $\zeta$ grids for temperature, the tangent grid, and all species.

\item\label{two} Interpolate {\tt phitan} from the {\tt ptan} grid to the
initial coarse zeta grid to get an initial set of tangent $\phi$s.

\item Use the {\tt two\_d\_hydrostatic} routine to compute a
reference height array on the initial coarse $\zeta$ grid and the
temperature $\phi$ basis.

\item Repeat

\begin{enumerate}

\item Calculate the minimum height for each $\zeta$ and its corresponding
$\phi$ using interpolation in the reference height array.  See {\tt
wvs-046}.

\item Repeat

\begin{enumerate}

\item Interpolate from the $\phi$ basis to the tangent $\phi$ in the
reference height array to get the tangent height for each $\zeta$.

\item Use the $\phi$ for the minimum height at each $\zeta$ as the
revised tangent $\phi$ for that $\zeta$.

\end{enumerate}

until the tangent $\phi$s don't change much.  The first estimate may be
good enough, in which case iteration and step (\ref{two}) won't be
necessary.

\item Calculate heights on the $\zeta$ grid along the line of sight for
each pointing, and calculate $\phi$s for each $\zeta$ along the line of
sight using those heights.

\item Using the $\phi$s and heights along each line of sight, the
height reference grid, and inverse interpolation, calculate $\zeta$s for
temperature basis $\phi$s for each pointing.

\item Augment the $\zeta$ grid using the newly-calculated $\zeta$s,
taking care not to insert new $\zeta$s too close to ones calculated in
step (\ref{one}) and replacing ones calculated in this step in a prior
iteration.

\item Use the {\tt two\_d\_hydrostatic} routine to compute a reference
height array on the augmented $\zeta$ grid and the temperature $\phi$
basis.

\end{enumerate}

until no new zetas are inserted and revised zetas are close to previously
inserted ones.  The first revision may be good enough.

\item Revise the {\tt Estimate\_tan\_phi} routine in {\tt
FullForwardModel\_m} to compute only the estimated spacecraft geocentric
altitude and line-of-sight velocity at the tangent points for each zeta
in the augmented coarse $\zeta$ grid, and rename it accordingly.

\item Insert GL zetas into the augmented grid.

\item Use the two\_d\_hydrostatic routine to compute
temperature and height reference arrays on the fine $\zeta$ grid and the
temperature $\phi$ basis.

\item Use the temperature and height reference arrays on the fine $\zeta$
grid to compute heights, $\phi$s and derivatives at each $\zeta$ along
each line of sight.

\end{enumerate}

